Comment (src/components/system-security-plans/SystemImplementationOverviewForm.vue:39):
**[Medium] In view mode this still renders as a form that looks editable — the disabled state has no visible affordance.**

Verified in the running app: before clicking Edit, the Remarks `Textarea` is functionally `disabled` but visually indistinguishable from an editable input — full border, white background, resize handle (screenshot-confirmed). The volt `Textarea` also lacks the legacy `FormTextarea`'s `disabled:cursor-not-allowed`, and the conditional `bg-gray-100` class here loses the specificity fight against the volt theme's own background utilities. On top of that it lost `w-full` (see the companion thread on the component create form), so the box renders shrunken with the label floating beside it.

Suggested fix: the cleanest option, consistent with the rest of this refactor (e.g. the new `StatementByComponent` read mode), is to render plain text/markdown in view mode and only mount the form fields when `isEditing` is true. If keeping the always-mounted form, add `w-full` and make the disabled state visually distinct (muted background + `cursor-not-allowed`) so users don't try to type into it.
