Comment (src/views/system-security-plans/SystemSecurityPlanSystemImplementationEditorView.vue:435):
**[High] Creating the first user silently never appears in the list — verified end-to-end in the running app.**

Repro through this modal: submit a valid user on an SSP with no users → POST returns **201 Created**, success toast shows, dialog closes — and the tab still reads "Users (0)" until a full page refresh.

Root cause (pre-existing handler, but this is the PR that makes these modals the primary editing flow, and it reproduces on the exact dialog touched here): the API returns `{"data": null}` for an empty collection, so `useDataApi` leaves `users.value === undefined`, and `handleUserCreated`'s `users.value?.push(newUser)` optional-chains into a **silent no-op**. The same pattern sits in `handleComponentCreated` and `handleLeveragedAuthCreated` — the first component/authorization created on an empty SSP vanishes the same way. (Non-empty lists only update by accident: the in-place `push` into `useDataApi`'s `shallowRef` isn't tracked, and the list only re-renders because closing the modal touches other reactive state in the same component.)

Suggested fix — one line per handler, replacing reference-mutation with assignment so it works for both the null case and the shallowRef:
```ts
users.value = [...(users.value ?? []), newUser];
```
(and equivalently for components / leveraged auths; the `handleXSaved` index-assignment variants deserve the same treatment.)
